==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pressman
<hw>Press"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pressmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
manages, or attends to, a press, esp. a printing press.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who presses clothes; <as>as, a tailor's
<ex>pressman</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pressman</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pressman
<hw>Press"man</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 2d <er>Press</er>.]</ety>
<def>One of a press gang, who aids in forcing men into the naval
service; also, one forced into the service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pressor</ent>⟦br⟧
